s of sexual celibacy but\n&gt; nevertheless accomplish the same ends (gradually, over time) of channeling\n&gt; healthily, controlling, and then overcoming the desire for sex. Also,\n&gt; forcible repression can have the opposite effet--flaring up of strong sexual\n&gt; urges that can be more problematic later on if healthy release is not\n&gt; allowed. A lot of problems in the Catholic church, ISKCON and now BAPS are\n&gt; attributable to this.\n\n\n"}}